title: Food Shortages
subtitle: We are suffering shortages of food
view-if: capital_strike_seen and spd_in_government and ((((class_war >= 1 and capital_strike_timer == 3 and (rural_spd+rural_kpd+rural_sapd <= rural_nsdap+rural_dnvp or (zca_formed and rural_spd+rural_kpd+rural_sapd <= rural_zca+rural_other+rural_dvp+rural_nsdap+rural_dnvp))) or socialized_land)) or (capital_flight and capital_strike_timer <= 5))
tags: event
max-visits: 2
on-arrival: capital_strike_timer -= 1; inflation += 2; inflation += 0.4 if not state_buyer; coalition_dissent += 1; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_grand_coalition; workers_spd -= 5; unemployed_spd -= 5; new_middle_spd -= 3; workers_zca += 5*bourgeois_power; new_middle_zca += 3

= Food Shortages

As we attempt to transition to socialism in our ongoing rupture with the bourgeoisie, we have encountered an obstacle in the form of the rural petty-bourgeoisie, upon whom we largely rely upon for food. Long a bastion of reaction, [? if land_reform : albeit limited in this by our land reform programs, ?] they have begun hoarding food out of hostility to our socialist project, causing prices to rise sharply-

- @state_buyer: We cannot begin to tackle this issue without a state buyer program.
- @meet: We will meet them at their new prices.
- @kill: We will force them to sell at the set price.
- @lower_tariffs: We will lower tariffs, so as to facilitate for importing deficit food.
- @reconcile_town_and_country: We will fund the development of urban agriculture, to work towards reconciling town and country.
- @root: There is nothing we can do.

@state_buyer
view-if: not state_buyer
subtitle: -2 budget.
on-arrival: state_buyer_vote = 1
go-to: legislative_menu if legislature_enabled; state_buyer_done if not legislature_enabled

We propose a bill to create a state monopoly for grain purchases.

@state_buyer_done
on-arrival: bourgeois_power -= 0.05; budget -= 2; state_buyer = 1; inflation -= 0.5 if inflation >= 3; workers_spd += 2*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 3*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 1 if (in_grand_coalition or in_weimar_coalition); dvp_relation -= 5; z_relation -= 3; rural_policy += 2; capital_strike_progress += 1; economic_growth += 0.4; socialism += 2

By initiating a state buyer program, we have facilitated for the proper tackling of this issue. Given the circumstances, however, farmers do not appreciate the creation of a state monopoly on grain purchases, seeing it as preparation for coercion against them to make them lower their prices. 

- @meet: They need not worry; we will meet their new prices.
- @kill: That they defy the economic plan is no fault of ours.
- @root: There is nothing more we can do.

@meet
view-if: state_buyer
subtitle: -1 budget
on-arrival: budget -= 1; pro_consumer += 1; inflation -= 0.6; rural_spd += 3*(1-dissent); workers_spd += 3*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 4*(1-dissent); workers_sol += 4; coalition_dissent += 1 if black_thursday_seen; economic_growth += 0.2

We cave to their demanded new prices. This helps ease the crisis significantly, and improves our reputation amongst farmers. Still, we will have to work harder, and some frown at our letting ourselves be bullied.

@kill
view-if: state_buyer
subtitle: This would spark quite the uproar against perceived Bolshevism.
on-arrival: socialism -= rural/10; socialism -= 6*bourgeois_power; black_market += (rural*(1-(rb_force+rfb_force)/100)); bourgeois_power -= 0.05; insurgency += 5; sh_militancy += 0.01; sa_militancy += 0.02; sa_strength += rural*insurgency; sh_strength += (rural*insurgency)/4; inflation -= 1; economic_growth -= black_market/10; rural_nsdap += 100; rural_dnvp += 100; rural_zca += 100 if zca_formed; rural_spd = 0; strife += 1; kpd_relation += 10; coup_progress += 5; west_relation -= 2; east_relation -= 2

We refuse to budge from our set prices, demanding that the farmers sell at the agreed price and cracking down harshly on those who continue to withhold their grain and demand more for it. The results see short term success, though some fear we are creating the long term conditions for a conflict between the country and the town, quite contrary to the reconciliation Marx hoped for. Indeed, the Harzburg Front swells, recruiting from dejected farmers.

@lower_tariffs
choose-if: tariffs > -5
subtitle: -2 budget. [? if tariffs <= -5 : There are no tariffs left to cut. ?]
on-arrival: tariff_cut_vote = 1
go-to: tariff_cut_done if not legislature_enabled; legislative_menu if legislature_enabled

We propose a bill to decrease tariff rates.

@tariff_cut_done
on-arrival: tariffs -= 1; budget -= 2; inflation -= 2; workers_spd += 4*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 4*(1-dissent); rural_spd -= 5; old_middle_spd -= 3; economic_growth += 0.4; socialism += 2; rural_zca += 10 if zca_formed; rural_nsdap += 10; rural_dnvp += 10; sa_strength += rural

By lowering tariffs, we alleviate much of the food crisis. However, farmers are not happy at being undercut and sidelined. While in the end, they are forced to meet the new market prices, it worsens their quality of life, and leads many to turn to the Harzburg Front.

Farmers are hurt by this policy, as cheap imported grain leads to ruin for some small producers. In general, cheap imports are detrimental for small-scale industries aimed at the domestic market.

@reconcile_town_and_country
view-if: not reconcile_town_and_country
subtitle: -3 budget. Many are skeptical; this does little to address the immediate crisis.
on-arrival: budget -= 3; inflation -= 0.2; inflation -= 0.5 if capital_flight; inflation -= nationalization_progress/10 if five_year_plan; coalition_dissent += 2; labor_dissent += 5; rural -= 1; workers += 1; reconcile_town_and_country

We have set aside significant funding towards the development of urban agriculture as a step towards the reconciliation of town and country, as advocated by Marx. I


